    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Stissing Mountain, the town’s tallest peak at 1,403 feet, is a 1.1‑billion‑year‑old Precambrian gneiss block that literally floats on younger shale.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
