      ],
      "source": "https://www.pineplains-ny.gov/homepage/about-pine-plains/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Pine Plains is rumored to have been a hidden stop on the Underground Railroad, aiding escaped slaves toward freedom.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.pineplains-ny.gov/homepage/about-pine-plains/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1798, Pine Plains opened the first public library in Dutchess County, a landmark of early civic learning.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
